@page "/docs"

<PageTitle>Rask · About</PageTitle>

<div class="max-w-3xl space-y-6">
    <div>
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">About Rask</h1>
        <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
            Rask is an open-source RabbitMQ management dashboard built by
            <a href="https://agdir.no" class="link link-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Agdir Drift AS</a>.
            Named after <strong>Ratatoskr</strong>, the Norse messenger squirrel that carries messages between
            the eagle at the top of Yggdrasil and the serpent at its roots.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Features</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-base-content/70">
            <li>Real-time overview with message rate charts and node status</li>
            <li>Queue management: peek, publish, purge, delete</li>
            <li>Exchange routing and topology visualization</li>
            <li>Live message tracing via AMQP</li>
            <li>Multi-environment support with encrypted credential storage</li>
            <li>Full admin: users, permissions, policies, vhosts, limits</li>
            <li>Import/export broker definitions</li>
            <li>Dark and light theme support</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Technology</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/70">
            Built with .NET 9, Blazor WebAssembly, ASP.NET Core, Tailwind CSS, and DaisyUI.
            Server-side proxying ensures your RabbitMQ credentials never leave the server.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
